  "root_text": {
    "sn5.8:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 5.8 ",
    "sn5.8:0.2": "1. Bhikkhunīvagga ",
    "sn5.8:0.3": "Sīsupacālāsutta ",
    "sn5.8:1.1": "Sāvatthinidānaṁ. ",
    "sn5.8:1.2": "Atha kho sīsupacālā bhikkhunī pubbaṇhasamayaṁ nivāsetvā …pe… ",
    "sn5.8:1.3": "aññatarasmiṁ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṁ nisīdi. ",
    "sn5.8:1.4": "Atha kho māro pāpimā yena sīsupacālā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā sīsupacālaṁ bhikkhuniṁ etadavoca: ",
    "sn5.8:1.5": "“kassa nu tvaṁ, bhikkhuni, pāsaṇḍaṁ rocesī”ti? ",
    "sn5.8:1.6": "“Na khvāhaṁ, āvuso, kassaci pāsaṇḍaṁ rocemī”ti. ",
    "sn5.8:2.1": "“Kaṁ nu uddissa muṇḍāsi, ",
    "sn5.8:2.2": "Samaṇī viya dissasi; ",
    "sn5.8:2.3": "Na ca rocesi pāsaṇḍaṁ, ",
    "sn5.8:2.4": "Kimiva carasi momūhā”ti. ",
    "sn5.8:3.1": "“Ito bahiddhā pāsaṇḍā, ",
    "sn5.8:3.2": "diṭṭhīsu pasīdanti te; ",
    "sn5.8:3.3": "Na tesaṁ dhammaṁ rocemi, ",
    "sn5.8:3.4": "te dhammassa akovidā. ",
    "sn5.8:4.1": "Atthi sakyakule jāto, ",
    "sn5.8:4.2": "buddho appaṭipuggalo; ",
    "sn5.8:4.3": "Sabbābhibhū māranudo, ",
    "sn5.8:4.4": "sabbatthamaparājito. ",
    "sn5.8:5.1": "Sabbattha mutto asito, ",
    "sn5.8:5.2": "sabbaṁ passati cakkhumā; ",
    "sn5.8:5.3": "Sabbakammakkhayaṁ patto, ",
    "sn5.8:5.4": "vimutto upadhisaṅkhaye; ",
    "sn5.8:5.5": "So mayhaṁ bhagavā satthā, ",
    "sn5.8:5.6": "tassa rocemi sāsanan”ti. ",
    "sn5.8:6.1": "Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṁ sīsupacālā bhikkhunī”ti dukkhī dummano tatthevantaradhāyīti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn5.8:0.1": "Linked Discourses 5.8 ",
    "sn5.8:0.2": "1. Nuns ",
    "sn5.8:0.3": "With Sīsupacālā ",
    "sn5.8:1.1": "At Sāvatthī. ",
    "sn5.8:1.2": "Then the nun Sīsupacālā robed up in the morning … ",
    "sn5.8:1.3": "and sat at the root of a tree for the day’s meditation. ",
    "sn5.8:1.4": "Then Māra the Wicked went up to Sīsupacālā and said to her, ",
    "sn5.8:1.5": "“Nun, whose creed do you approve of?” ",
    "sn5.8:1.6": "“I don’t approve anyone’s creed, sir.” ",
    "sn5.8:2.1": "“In whose name did you shave your head? ",
    "sn5.8:2.2": "You look like an ascetic, ",
    "sn5.8:2.3": "but you don’t approve any creed. ",
    "sn5.8:2.4": "Why do you wander as if lost?” ",
    "sn5.8:3.1": "“Followers of other creeds ",
    "sn5.8:3.2": "are confident in their views. ",
    "sn5.8:3.3": "But I don’t approve their teaching, ",
    "sn5.8:3.4": "for they’re no experts in the Dhamma. ",
    "sn5.8:4.1": "But there is one born in the Sakyan clan, ",
    "sn5.8:4.2": "the unrivaled Buddha, ",
    "sn5.8:4.3": "champion, dispeller of Māra, ",
    "sn5.8:4.4": "everywhere undefeated, ",
    "sn5.8:5.1": "everywhere freed, and unattached, ",
    "sn5.8:5.2": "the Clear-eyed One sees all. ",
    "sn5.8:5.3": "He has attained the end of all deeds, ",
    "sn5.8:5.4": "freed with the ending of attachments. ",
    "sn5.8:5.5": "That Blessed One is my Teacher, ",
    "sn5.8:5.6": "and I approve his instruction.” ",
    "sn5.8:6.1": "Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The nun Sīsupacālā knows me!” miserable and sad, vanished right there. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "sn5.8:1.2": "sīsupacālā → sīsūpacālā (bj) "
  },
